WEBVTT

00:01.542 --> 00:02.500
<i>PREVIOUSLY ON</i>
<i>"RED BAND SOCIETY"...</i>

00:02.583 --> 00:03.875
YOU'RE BURNING UP.
NO, NO.

00:03.959 --> 00:05.000
I'M JUST A LITTLE WARM.
ARE YOU SURE?

00:05.083 --> 00:06.375
[ GASPS ]
HUNTER, HUNTER!

00:06.458 --> 00:09.041
MY JOB IS TO PROTECT
YOUR HEART, KARA,

00:09.125 --> 00:10.625
IN EVERY POSSIBLE WAY.

00:10.709 --> 00:12.333
EMANCIPATION SEEMS LIKE
AN APPEALING OPTION.

00:12.417 --> 00:13.834
ALL WE NEED
IS THE FILING FEE.

00:13.917 --> 00:15.542
$395.

00:15.625 --> 00:16.959
Kara: OH, MY GOD,
IS THAT DELANEY SHAW?

00:17.041 --> 00:18.166
I WAS WONDERING
IF YOU'D BE COMFORTABLE

00:18.250 --> 00:19.625
INTRODUCING ME
TO YOUR MANAGER.

00:19.709 --> 00:21.667
I WILL GIVE YOU 10 MINUTES
FOR 10 PAINKILLERS.

00:21.750 --> 00:23.834
Dr. McAndrew:
I WAS KIND OF THINKING

00:23.917 --> 00:26.834
THIS IS LIKE A ONE-TIME THING,
YOU KNOW?
Brittany: I <i>DON'T.</i>

00:26.917 --> 00:28.959
HAVEN'T YOU EVER HAD
A ONE-NIGHT STAND BEFORE?

00:29.041 --> 00:30.250
OW!

00:30.333 --> 00:31.417
I HAD MY MEETING
WITH DR. SAMUELS,

00:31.500 --> 00:32.709
AND SHE SAID
THAT I COULD GO.

00:32.792 --> 00:33.959
EMMA, YOU CAN'T GO.
YOU'RE STILL SICK.

00:34.041 --> 00:35.333
YOU CAN'T JUST LEAVE!

00:35.417 --> 00:37.125
ALL PACKED UP?
DAD, THIS IS LEO.

00:37.208 --> 00:38.458
PLEASED TO MEET YOU.

00:38.542 --> 00:40.542
LEO, IS IT?
IT WAS NICE TO MEET YOU.

00:43.208 --> 00:48.291
Charlie: <i>THE GREAT PHILOSOPHER</i>
<i>TUPAC SHAKUR ONCE SAID,</i>

00:48.375 --> 00:53.125
<i>YOU CAN SPEND MINUTES, HOURS,</i>
<i>DAYS, WEEKS, OR EVEN MONTHS</i>

00:53.208 --> 00:55.125
<i>OVERANALYZING A SITUATION,</i>

00:55.208 --> 00:57.709
<i>TRYING TO PUT</i>
<i>THE PIECES TOGETHER...</i>

00:59.208 --> 01:01.291
<i>OR YOU CAN JUST LEAVE</i>
<i>THE PIECES ON THE FLOOR</i>

01:01.375 --> 01:03.000
<i>AND MOVE ON.</i>

01:03.083 --> 01:06.041
<i>THERE MAY HAVE BEEN</i>
<i>SOME SWEAR WORDS IN THERE,</i>

01:06.125 --> 01:07.542
<i>BUT THAT WAS THE GIST.</i>

01:07.625 --> 01:11.208
I JUST CAN'T BELIEVE
SHE LEFT

01:11.291 --> 01:13.166
WITHOUT SAYING GOODBYE
TO ANYONE.

01:13.250 --> 01:14.750
SHE SAID GOODBYE
TO LEO.

01:14.834 --> 01:16.750
SOMEWHAT.

01:16.834 --> 01:20.875
YEAH, BUT TO JUST TAKE OFF?
THAT'S NOT LIKE EMMA.

01:20.959 --> 01:22.291
THAT SOUNDS
<i>EXACTLY</i> LIKE EMMA.

01:22.375 --> 01:23.917
SHE'S ALL
ABOUT BEING ELUSIVE.

01:24.041 --> 01:25.583
YOU THOUGHT THAT YOU KNEW HER,
BUT YOU DIDN'T.

01:25.667 --> 01:27.625
NONE OF US DID, WHICH IS EXACTLY
WHAT SHE WANTED.

01:27.709 --> 01:29.458
GIVE IT A REST,
KARA.

01:29.542 --> 01:31.291
WHY?
YOU THINK I'M WRONG?

01:31.375 --> 01:34.834
I THINK NO ONE'S INTERESTED
IN LISTENING TO YOUR CRAP TODAY.

01:34.917 --> 01:37.250
TESTY.

01:37.333 --> 01:38.542
DID SHE SAY ANYTHING
TO YOU, LEO?

01:41.750 --> 01:43.792
I'M NOT BETTER, OKAY?
I'M NOT BETTER!

01:43.875 --> 01:46.041
AND I KEEP WAITING FOR SOMEONE
TO FIGURE THAT OUT,

01:46.125 --> 01:47.291
AND THEY DON'T!

01:47.375 --> 01:49.542
NOT REALLY.

01:49.625 --> 01:52.250
WHO PICKED HER UP?
HER DAD.

01:52.333 --> 01:53.750
I DON'T THINK
HER MOM HAS BEEN HERE

01:53.834 --> 01:55.417
SINCE SHE WAS
FIRST ADMITTED.

01:55.500 --> 01:57.834
SERIOUSLY?
I DIDN'T KNOW THAT.

01:57.917 --> 01:59.083
LIKE I SAID,
WE DON'T KNOW JACK.

01:59.166 --> 02:00.542
SHUT UP!

02:00.625 --> 02:02.792
SHUT THE HELL UP
FOR ONCE IN YOUR LIFE!

02:05.542 --> 02:06.917
I JUST...

02:07.000 --> 02:10.500
I CAN'T IMAGINE THIS PLACE
WITHOUT EMMA.

02:10.583 --> 02:13.667
ME NEITHER.

02:13.750 --> 02:16.208
I GUESS SOMEONE
HAD TO BE THE FIRST TO GO.

02:16.291 --> 02:18.625
<i>WHICH BEGS THE QUESTION...</i>

02:18.709 --> 02:21.750
<i>WHO WILL BE NEXT?</i>

02:21.834 --> 02:24.583
KNIGHT TO C3.

02:24.667 --> 02:26.083
[ CLICK ]

02:26.166 --> 02:27.875
YOUR MOVE, LITTLE MAN.

02:27.959 --> 02:29.875
<i>NOW WOULD PROBABLY BE</i>
<i>A GOOD TIME</i>

02:29.959 --> 02:32.500
<i>TO TELL DR. NADAY I DON'T</i>
<i>KNOW HOW TO PLAY CHESS.</i>

02:35.542 --> 02:38.000
[ <i>CLICKING</i> ]
[ P.A. BEEPS ]

02:38.083 --> 02:40.041
Woman: <i>DR. McANDREW,</i>
<i>YOU HAVE A CALL ON LINE THREE.</i>

02:40.125 --> 02:41.834
<i>DR. McANDREW,</i>
<i>CALL ON LINE THREE.</i>

02:41.917 --> 02:45.375
YOU WANT ME TO MOVE
YOUR <i>PRAWN</i> TO D5?

02:45.458 --> 02:49.083
Charlie:
<i>I'M ALSO NOT THE BEST TYPIST.</i>

02:49.166 --> 02:52.500
<i>PAWN</i> TO D5.
GOOD. OKAY.

02:52.583 --> 02:54.917
PAWN -- D5.

02:55.000 --> 02:56.667
[ CLICK ]

02:56.750 --> 02:59.917
YOU KNOW YOU WANT TO
HIT THAT, RIGHT?

03:00.000 --> 03:02.166
<i>I DO. I</i> REALLY <i>DO.</i>

03:02.250 --> 03:05.083
ALL RIGHT.
I'LL HELP YOU OUT.

03:09.792 --> 03:11.709
ALL RIGHT.

03:11.792 --> 03:17.625
NOW...ALL YOU HAVE TO DO
IS MOVE THAT FINGER <i>THERE.</i>

03:17.709 --> 03:22.208
GOOD MORNING, CHARLIE.
DR. NADAY.

03:22.291 --> 03:24.875
[ <i>CLICKING</i> ]
MORNING.

03:24.959 --> 03:27.000
CHARLIE SAYS...

03:27.083 --> 03:28.166
[ CHUCKLES ]

03:28.250 --> 03:29.542
"GOOD MORTING
NOOSE JASKON."

03:29.625 --> 03:33.166
[ CHUCKLES ]
I'LL TAKE IT.

03:33.250 --> 03:35.333
YOU KNOW, I...

03:35.417 --> 03:38.000
STILL DON'T UNDERSTAND
HOW ALL THIS WORKS EXACTLY.

03:38.083 --> 03:39.792
IT'S AN
EYE-TRACKING DEVICE.

03:39.875 --> 03:42.500
IT USES GAZE INTERACTION
TO REPLACE THE STANDARD MOUSE.

03:42.583 --> 03:44.375
IT'S CALIBRATED
TO CHARLIE'S EYES.

03:44.458 --> 03:46.375
LET ME REPHRASE.

03:46.458 --> 03:48.000
I'M HAPPY
THAT IT ALL WORKS

03:48.083 --> 03:50.041
AND THAT I DON'T
<i>HAVE</i> TO UNDERSTAND.

03:50.125 --> 03:51.834
I SEE WE HAVE A LUDDITE
AMONG US.

03:51.917 --> 03:55.208
OH, NOT ENTIRELY.
I DO OWN A SMARTPHONE.

03:55.291 --> 03:56.875
REALLY?
GOOD TO KNOW.

03:56.959 --> 04:00.542
SO, UH,
WHAT IS THE END GAME HERE?

04:00.625 --> 04:03.375
WELL, HOPEFULLY,
THIS IS JUST A STOPGAP MEASURE

04:03.458 --> 04:05.291
UNTIL CHARLIE REGAINS
HIS FULL FACULTIES.

04:05.375 --> 04:08.709
RIGHT NOW, WE'RE WORKING ON
GETTING HIM TO MOVE ONE FINGER.

04:08.792 --> 04:10.375
ISN'T THAT RIGHT,
LITTLE MAN?

04:10.458 --> 04:12.417
I'M <i>WORKING ON IT.</i>

04:12.500 --> 04:14.917
<i>YOU'RE WORKING ON GETTING</i>
<i>NURSE JACKSON'S PHONE NUMBER.</i>

04:15.000 --> 04:17.417
THERE YOU ARE. UH, DR. POTTER
NEEDS YOU IN ROOM 211.

04:17.500 --> 04:19.083
OH,
YOU CAN'T LEAVE NOW.

04:19.166 --> 04:20.792
CHARLIE'S ABOUT
TO MAKE HIS MOVE.

04:20.875 --> 04:23.125
ACTUALLY, I THINK
IT'S <i>YOUR</i> MOVE, DOCTOR.

04:23.208 --> 04:24.709
[ PEN CLICKS ]

04:29.333 --> 04:32.250
SHE'S HERE! EMMA!

04:32.333 --> 04:34.250
HEY, FINN.

04:34.333 --> 04:36.041
AM I CRAZY,
OR DID YOU GET TALLER?

04:36.125 --> 04:37.250
YEP,
LIKE HALF AN INCH.

04:37.333 --> 04:38.625
I'M ON
THE VOLLEYBALL TEAM NOW.

04:38.709 --> 04:40.291
THAT'S SO COOL!

04:40.375 --> 04:43.125
GOOD LORD, I DIDN'T REALIZE
YOU HAD SO MUCH STUFF THERE.

04:43.208 --> 04:45.250
I GUESS TWO MONTHS
IS A LONG TIME.

04:45.333 --> 04:46.792
IT FELT
LIKE TWO YEARS.

04:46.875 --> 04:48.542
THERE'S SO MUCH
I HAVE TO CATCH YOU UP ON.

04:48.625 --> 04:49.875
FINLEY, HONEY, GIVE YOUR SISTER
A CHANCE TO BREATHE.

04:49.959 --> 04:53.000
[ Chuckling ]
COME HERE, YOU.

04:53.083 --> 04:55.417
HI, MOM.

04:55.500 --> 04:57.667
HEY, HONEY.

05:01.625 --> 05:03.208
LOOK AT YOUR HAIR.
IT'S GOTTEN SO LONG.

05:03.291 --> 05:05.166
OH, YEAH, I'VE, UM,
BEEN GROWING IT OUT.

05:05.250 --> 05:06.667
PROBABLY NEED
TO GET IT CUT.

05:06.750 --> 05:08.500
OH, NO, NO,
I LIKE IT THIS WAY.

05:08.583 --> 05:10.542
Finley:
YOU HAVE TO COME SEE MY ROOM.

05:10.625 --> 05:12.417
I GOT A TON OF NEW POSTERS.
COME ON. COME ON!

05:12.500 --> 05:14.750
[ CHUCKLES ]
YES, SHE DOES.

05:14.834 --> 05:15.917
[ SIGHS ]

05:16.000 --> 05:17.917
HEY, ARE YOU OKAY?

05:18.000 --> 05:20.542
FINN, DON'T PULL
ON YOUR SISTER SO HARD.

05:20.625 --> 05:22.375
UH, S-SHE DIDN'T.
I JUST TRIPPED.

05:22.458 --> 05:24.625
YOU SURE YOU'RE NOT DIZZY?
DAD, REALLY, I'M FINE.

05:24.709 --> 05:28.250
COME ON. SHOW ME THOSE POSTERS.
[ CHUCKLES ]

05:30.333 --> 05:32.083
SHE STILL LOOKS THIN.

05:32.166 --> 05:34.667
AH,
SHE'S ALWAYS BEEN THIN.

05:34.750 --> 05:37.291
JORDI,
YOU HAVE A VISITOR.

05:37.375 --> 05:39.041
I DO? WHO IS IT?

05:39.125 --> 05:41.375
HELLO, SEXY.

05:41.458 --> 05:43.208
WELL, I GUESS THAT ANSWERS
<i>THAT</i> QUESTION.

05:43.291 --> 05:45.125
DON'T FORGET THAT...

05:45.208 --> 05:48.291
YOU HAVE, UH, YOUR FIRST
PET SCAN IN ABOUT AN HOUR,

05:48.375 --> 05:51.625
AND, UH, DR. McANDREW WILL --
OKAY, ALL RIGHT, THEN.

05:51.709 --> 05:53.250
[ CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY ]
YOU KIDS HAVE FUN.

05:53.333 --> 05:55.959
UM...
[ SIGHS ]

05:56.041 --> 05:58.417
AS MUCH
AS I'M ENJOYING THIS,

05:58.500 --> 05:59.667
I THINK YOU HAVE
THE WRONG JORDI.

05:59.750 --> 06:01.208
I DON'T THINK SO.

06:01.291 --> 06:03.542
DELANEY SAID YOU WERE HOT,
VAGUELY LATINO.

06:03.625 --> 06:06.542
DELANEY? WAIT,
A-ARE YOU A PART OF HER TEAM?

06:06.625 --> 06:08.750
DID SHE CHANGE HER MIND ABOUT
LETTING ME PLAY FOR YOU GUYS?

06:08.834 --> 06:10.166
[ CHUCKLES ]

06:10.250 --> 06:11.750
I HAVE NO IDEA
WHAT YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT,

06:11.834 --> 06:13.375
AND I'M NOT TECHNICALLY A PART
OF HER "TEAM,"

06:13.458 --> 06:14.750
BUT I WAS HOPING I COULD

06:14.834 --> 06:16.208
GET THE "FRIENDS AND FAMILY"
DISCOUNT?

06:16.291 --> 06:17.959
THE WHAT?

06:18.041 --> 06:19.625
FINE,
I'LL PAY FULL PRICE.

06:19.709 --> 06:22.792
BUT I WANT THE GOOD STUFF --
NOTHING GENERIC.

06:22.875 --> 06:25.583
HOLD UP.
A-ARE YOU HERE FOR DRUGS?

06:25.667 --> 06:27.083
[ Chuckling ]
DUDE, KEEP IT DOWN.

06:27.166 --> 06:29.583
I CAN'T BELIEVE THIS.
GET OUT OF MY ROOM!

06:29.667 --> 06:31.000
WHOA!

06:31.083 --> 06:32.291
WHY SO SENSITIVE?

06:32.375 --> 06:33.834
I'M GIVING YOU
ONE MORE MINUTE,

06:33.917 --> 06:35.417
AND THEN
I'M CALLING SECURITY.

06:45.834 --> 06:48.250
IN CASE
YOU CHANGE YOUR MIND.

07:03.750 --> 07:05.458
UH, ARE YOU GOING
TO CHECK ON HUNTER?

07:05.542 --> 07:06.875
SMART <i>AND</i> PRETTY.

07:06.959 --> 07:08.333
BRING THOSE BABIES UP
TO A "C" CUP,

07:08.417 --> 07:09.750
AND YOU COULD BE
A TRIPLE THREAT.

07:09.834 --> 07:12.250
NO, UH, YOU CAN'T GO THERE
RIGHT NOW.

07:12.333 --> 07:13.667
WHY NOT?

07:13.750 --> 07:15.375
IT'S NOT BAD.
IT'S JUST NOT A GOOD TIME.

07:15.458 --> 07:17.417
DR. McANDREW'S IN THERE,
TALKING TO HIS PARENTS.

07:17.500 --> 07:18.959
IT SOUNDS LIKE
THE PERFECT TIME TO ME.

07:19.041 --> 07:20.625
THE ONLY WAY TO FIND OUT
WHAT'S REALLY GOING ON

07:20.709 --> 07:21.875
IS WHEN THE PARENTS
ARE AROUND.

07:21.959 --> 07:23.667
THAT'S NOT TRUE.

07:23.750 --> 07:25.375
OKAY,
IT'S SOMETIMES TRUE.

07:25.458 --> 07:28.625
BUT...

07:28.709 --> 07:30.458
SO,
HOW HIGH WAS THE FEVER?

07:30.542 --> 07:33.208
GOT UP TO 103.
OH, MY GOD.

07:33.291 --> 07:36.083
WE DID A CHEST X-RAY.
WE GAVE HIM SOME BLOOD TESTS.

07:36.166 --> 07:39.375
EVERYTHING HAS BEEN REASSURING.
THERE'S NO SIGN OF INFECTION.

07:39.458 --> 07:40.792
SO,
WHAT CAUSED THE FEVER?

07:40.875 --> 07:42.125
WE STOPPED ONE
OF HIS MEDICATIONS

07:42.208 --> 07:44.333
THAT WE GAVE HIM
ON ADMISSION

07:44.417 --> 07:46.333
WHERE FEVERS
ARE A KNOWN SIDE EFFECT.

07:46.417 --> 07:47.750
UH, HE'S BEEN AFEBRILE
SO FAR TODAY,

07:47.834 --> 07:49.625
SO MY GUESS IS
THAT WAS THE CULPRIT.

07:49.709 --> 07:52.417
YOU GUYS NEED TO RELAX.
I FEEL TOTALLY FINE NOW.

07:52.500 --> 07:53.750
ASIDE FROM THE BUNK LIVER

07:53.834 --> 07:55.583
AND THE LIFE-THREATENING
ILLNESS,

07:55.667 --> 07:59.000
I AM THE PICTURE OF HEALTH.

08:00.166 --> 08:03.458
CAN I JUST ASK, W-WHAT'S MY SON
STILL DOING HERE?

08:03.542 --> 08:04.959
I MEAN, I KNOW WE'RE WAITING
ON A NEW LIVER,

08:05.041 --> 08:07.959
BUT SINCE WE HAVE NO IDEA
WHEN IT WILL COME --

08:08.041 --> 08:10.458
WE JUST --
JUST WANT TO TAKE HIM HOME.

08:10.542 --> 08:12.500
UNLESS YOU CAN GIVE US
A REASON NOT TO.

08:12.583 --> 08:15.083
JUST WANT TO KEEP MY EYE ON HIM
FOR A FEW MORE HOURS,

08:15.166 --> 08:16.834
MAKE SURE THAT FEVER
DOESN'T CREEP BACK UP,

08:16.917 --> 08:19.583
BUT AFTER THAT, YOU KNOW,
IT'S COMPLETELY YOUR DECISION.

08:19.667 --> 08:22.250
[ SIGHS ]
I MEAN, IT'S UP TO YOU --

08:22.333 --> 08:24.750
WHEREVER YOU FEEL
MORE COMFORTABLE, HONEY.

08:24.834 --> 08:27.917
I WANT TO GO HOME
WITH YOU GUYS.

08:28.000 --> 08:30.083
[ SIGHS ] GREAT.

08:30.166 --> 08:31.709
THEN DAD WILL GO DEAL
WITH THE PAPERWORK,

08:31.792 --> 08:33.375
AND WE'LL GET YOU HOME --
TODAY.

08:33.458 --> 08:35.417
[ DAVID CHUCKLES ]

08:35.500 --> 08:37.000
THANKS, DOC.

08:44.125 --> 08:47.125
-- Captions by VITAC --
www.vitac.com

08:50.417 --> 08:53.250
[ WHISTLING ]

08:53.333 --> 08:56.750
♪ INSIDE MY HEART,
THERE'S AN EMPTY NEST ♪

08:56.834 --> 09:01.250
♪ A HEAVY HATE
ON A HOLLOW CHEST ♪

09:01.333 --> 09:05.625
♪ SOFT-SPOKEN LIKE A DISEASE ♪

09:05.709 --> 09:09.041
♪ IS THE WAY TO INCOMPLETE ME ♪

09:09.125 --> 09:13.875
♪ CAN YOU SHAKE
THIS HOLLOW NIGHT? ♪

09:13.959 --> 09:17.709
♪ TELL YOUR TRUTH
OR TRUST A LIE ♪

09:17.792 --> 09:22.041
♪ IS THIS HELLO,
OR IS IT GOODBYE? ♪

09:22.125 --> 09:27.166
♪ IS THIS THE LOW,
OR IS THIS THE HI-I-I-IGH? ♪

09:27.250 --> 09:30.875
♪ JUST LET IT GO,
ENJOY THE RI-I-I-I-DE ♪

09:30.959 --> 09:34.875
♪ WITHOUT THE LOW,
THERE AIN'T A HI-I-IGH ♪

09:34.959 --> 09:37.375
♪ HI-IGH-IGH-IGH-IGH ♪

09:37.458 --> 09:40.291
[ WHISTLING ]

09:44.291 --> 09:46.375
HEY, YOU.

09:46.458 --> 09:48.125
HOLD ON A SEC.

09:48.208 --> 09:50.166
YO, HAIRNET, YOU GOT ANY FRUIT
THAT ISN'T DISGUSTING?

09:50.250 --> 09:52.583
THESE BANANAS ARE AS BROWN
AS MY ROOTS.

09:53.583 --> 09:56.250
YOU KNOW WHAT? SKIP IT.
I'M NOT EVEN HUNGRY.
KARA.

09:56.333 --> 09:57.750
ALL RIGHT, WHAT'S UP?

09:57.834 --> 09:58.917
CAN WE TALK
FOR A SECOND?

09:59.000 --> 10:00.500
WHAT ABOUT?

10:00.583 --> 10:02.417
YOU KNOW THAT I DON'T
WANT TO LEAVE, RIGHT?

10:02.500 --> 10:04.583
I'D MUCH RATHER SPEND WHATEVER
DAYS I HAVE LEFT ON THIS EARTH

10:04.667 --> 10:07.542
MAKING ROTTEN BANANA JOKES
WITH YOU. IT'S JUST MY MOM --

10:07.625 --> 10:09.417
OH, MY GOD. PLEASE DON'T GET
ALL NICHOLAS SPARKS ON ME.

10:09.500 --> 10:12.041
THIS IS SO NOT A CONVERSATION
WE NEED TO HAVE.

10:12.125 --> 10:14.208
I WANT TO HAVE IT.
I DON'T!

10:14.291 --> 10:16.667
YOU'RE ANGRY. I GET IT.
NO, I'M NOT ANGRY.

10:16.750 --> 10:19.166
I'D HAVE TO CARE.GRY,

10:19.250 --> 10:21.583
BUT...ENSE OR ANYTHING,

10:21.667 --> 10:23.333
I BARELY EVEN KNOW YOU.

10:23.417 --> 10:24.959
THIS WAS JUST A HANG.

10:25.041 --> 10:28.250
OKAY. COOL.

10:30.917 --> 10:33.500
HAVE A NICE LIFE,
HUNTER COLE.

10:33.583 --> 10:35.583
YEAH. YOU TOO.

10:38.750 --> 10:40.333
ANYWAY, UH...

10:40.417 --> 10:43.166
ANYWAY, I'M RAMBLING NOW.

10:43.250 --> 10:44.667
CALL ME WHEN YOU GET THIS.

10:44.750 --> 10:46.500
I JUST WANT TO...

10:46.583 --> 10:49.500
I JUST WANT TO HEAR YOUR VOICE,
MAKE SURE Y-YOU'RE, UH...

10:49.583 --> 10:51.000
YOU'RE OKAY.

10:51.083 --> 10:53.500
EMMA, I-I-I...

10:53.583 --> 10:55.000
I MISS YOU.

10:55.083 --> 10:57.667
[ SIGHS ] DEAR GOD, MAN,
HAVE YOU NO SHAME?

10:57.750 --> 10:59.125
I'M JUST
CHECKING IN ON HER.

10:59.208 --> 11:00.667
NO.
YOU'RE JUST STALKING HER.

11:00.750 --> 11:02.667
YOU NEED TO GET A GRIP

11:02.750 --> 11:04.792
BEFORE THIS TURNS INTO THE
TRAGIC MOVIE OF THE WEEK --

11:04.875 --> 11:06.417
"MOTHER, MAY I SLEEP
WITH CANCER?"

11:06.500 --> 11:08.250
YOU'RE, LIKE, ON STEROIDS TODAY.
WHAT IS YOUR PROBLEM?

11:08.333 --> 11:09.917
EVERYTHING!

11:10.000 --> 11:11.250
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

11:11.333 --> 11:13.250
OUT.
OUT WHERE?

11:13.333 --> 11:15.125
OUT OF THIS
FREAKING HOSPITAL.

11:15.208 --> 11:17.000
I'M TAKING
A SENIOR DITCH DAY.

11:17.083 --> 11:18.417
YOU ASKED NURSE JACKSON?

11:18.500 --> 11:19.834
NO, LEO.

11:19.917 --> 11:21.208
ASKING NURSE JACKSON
WOULD DEFEAT THE PURPOSE

11:21.291 --> 11:23.417
OF A DITCH DAY
ON EVERY POSSIBLE LEVEL.

11:23.500 --> 11:27.000
OKAY, SO, UM, WHAT,
YOU HAVE A CAR?

11:27.083 --> 11:28.500
I'M FROM BEVERLY HILLS.

11:28.583 --> 11:30.166
I HAVE TWO CARS,
ONE OF WHICH IS ON ITS WAY.

11:30.250 --> 11:32.417
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

11:32.500 --> 11:33.792
OKAY,
I'LL MAKE A DEAL WITH YOU.

11:33.875 --> 11:35.458
I WON'T TELL NURSE JACKSON

11:35.542 --> 11:37.083
ANYTHING IF YOU GIVE ME
A LIFT TO EMMA'S HOUSE.

11:37.166 --> 11:39.500
[ SCOFFS ]
YOU ARE SUCH A WHINY BITCH!

11:39.583 --> 11:41.709
YOU HAVE FIVE SECONDS.

11:42.625 --> 11:44.125
JUST GET IN.

11:48.959 --> 11:51.500
[ SIGHS ]

11:57.333 --> 11:58.417
[ DRAWER OPENS ]

11:58.500 --> 12:00.333
[ SNIFFS ]

12:19.083 --> 12:22.166
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

12:22.250 --> 12:24.834
[ SPRAYING ]

12:24.917 --> 12:26.917
HEY.
HOW'S IT GOING?

12:27.000 --> 12:27.959
FINE.

12:28.041 --> 12:29.500
YOU NEED ANYTHING?

12:29.583 --> 12:30.750
NOPE, I'M GOOD.
THANKS.

12:33.625 --> 12:35.417
WHEN YOU'RE READY,

12:35.500 --> 12:37.542
WE SHOULD TALK ABOUT SCHOOL
AND ALL YOUR EXTRACURRICULARS.

12:37.625 --> 12:39.500
I-I'VE BEEN THINKING
ABOUT IT,

12:39.583 --> 12:42.375
AND MAYBE YOU WERE A LITTLE
OVEREXTENDED BEFORE.

12:42.458 --> 12:44.417
YEAH, WHATEVER
YOU THINK IS BEST.

12:44.500 --> 12:47.083
I DON'T KNOW WHAT'S BEST
FOR YOU, EMMA.

12:47.166 --> 12:49.166
I'M GONNA
NEED YOUR HELP.

12:51.291 --> 12:53.375
HOW COME
YOU NEVER VISITED ME?

12:53.458 --> 12:54.875
I DID VISIT YOU.

12:54.959 --> 12:56.291
IN THE BEGINNING,

12:56.375 --> 12:57.792
BUT I HAVEN'T SEEN YOU
IN ALMOST THREE WEEKS.

12:59.792 --> 13:02.250
NEVER MIND.
IT DOESN'T MATTER.

13:02.333 --> 13:04.417
NO, I-I-IT D--
IT MATTERS.

13:04.500 --> 13:05.834
IT DOES.

13:07.667 --> 13:10.417
HONEY, THE FIRST FEW TIMES
I CAME TO SEE YOU,

13:10.500 --> 13:12.917
I FELT LIKE, OH...

13:13.041 --> 13:15.125
I DIDN'T
KNOW WHAT TO SAY.

13:15.208 --> 13:17.458
I GOT SO SCARED I WAS GONNA SAY
THE WRONG THING.

13:17.542 --> 13:20.000
THE WRONG THING WOULD HAVE
BEEN BETTER THAN NOTHING.

13:20.083 --> 13:21.458
I DON'T KNOW
THAT THAT'S TRUE.

13:21.542 --> 13:24.250
[ SIGHS ]
I'VE BEEN GOING TO GROUPS.

13:24.333 --> 13:28.250
PARENTS WHO HAVE CHILDREN
WITH SIMILAR...

13:28.333 --> 13:29.625
YOU KNOW, ISSUES.

13:29.709 --> 13:31.250
I WANTED TO
EDUCATE MYSELF

13:31.333 --> 13:33.667
SO THAT I COULD BE BETTER,
HELP YOU GET BETTER.

13:33.750 --> 13:36.458
ONE OF THE MOMS,
HER DAUGHTER...

13:36.542 --> 13:39.792
DIED.

13:39.875 --> 13:41.166
CAN YOU IMAGINE?

13:41.250 --> 13:42.792
I'M OKAY NOW, MOM.
YOU DON'T HAVE TO WORRY.

13:42.875 --> 13:44.291
THE MORE I READ,

13:44.375 --> 13:45.750
THE MORE I COULDN'T STOP
THINKING OF GRANDMA.

13:45.834 --> 13:46.750
GRANDMA?

13:46.834 --> 13:49.917
NO,
I-IT DOESN'T MATTER.

13:50.000 --> 13:51.583
NO, WAIT,
W-WHAT ABOUT GRANDMA?

13:51.667 --> 13:53.375
POINT IS,
YOU BEAT THIS.

13:53.458 --> 13:55.875
EMMA,
YOU DID THE WORK,

13:55.959 --> 13:59.333
AND NOW YOU'RE HOME
BECAUSE YOU ARE STRONG.

13:59.417 --> 14:01.083
I'M SO PROUD OF YOU.

14:04.834 --> 14:07.250
HOW IS "JEM"
NOT A WORD?

14:07.333 --> 14:08.834
IT'S A WORD.

14:08.917 --> 14:10.667
IT'S A WORD THAT STARTS
WITH THE LETTER "G."

14:10.750 --> 14:15.834
NOT THE DOLL.
THE DOLL STARTS WITH A "J."

14:15.917 --> 14:18.166
♪ JEM IS
TRULY OUTRAGEOUS ♪

14:18.250 --> 14:20.000
♪ TRULY, TRULY,
TRULY OUTRAGEOUS ♪

14:20.083 --> 14:21.417
[ LAUGHS ]
I KNOW THE SONG.

14:21.500 --> 14:22.750
I JUST WANTED TO SEE
IF YOU'D SING.

14:22.834 --> 14:24.417
[ SCOFFS ]
[ LAUGHS ]

14:24.500 --> 14:28.417
HEY, HAVE EITHER OF YOU SEEN --
UH, SEEN JORDI?

14:28.500 --> 14:30.250
UH, HE WAS HERE
A MINUTE AGO.

14:30.333 --> 14:31.625
DID YOU NEED ME
TO FIND HIM?

14:31.709 --> 14:33.458
UH, NO, IT'S NOT URGENT.
IT'S JUST, UH,

14:33.542 --> 14:35.625
JORDI'S GONNA BE WAITING
ON HIS PET-SCAN RESULTS,

14:35.709 --> 14:39.208
AND I FIGURED
HE COULD USE A FRIEND.

14:39.291 --> 14:41.542
UH, WELL,
I CAN CHECK IN WITH JORDI,

14:41.625 --> 14:43.000
MAKE SURE
HE'S DOING OKAY.

14:43.083 --> 14:44.458
THANKS, KENJI.

14:44.542 --> 14:47.583
EXCUSE ME.

14:50.000 --> 14:53.125
Kenji: ARE YOU LOOKING
FOR SOMETHING?

14:53.208 --> 14:55.500
I SWEAR I USED TO KEEP
A LIP GLOSS IN HERE.

14:55.583 --> 14:57.166
I HAVEN'T SEEN
YOU WEAR LIP GLOSS

14:57.250 --> 14:58.667
SINCE MADONNA
WAS RELEVANT.

14:58.750 --> 15:00.250
OH.

15:02.333 --> 15:04.417
WHAT WAS <i>THAT</i> ABOUT?

15:04.500 --> 15:07.417
DON'T YOU HAVE ANY ACTUAL
DOCTOR WORK TO DO?

15:12.000 --> 15:13.834
WHO AM I KIDDING?
[ CHUCKLES ]

15:13.917 --> 15:15.834
I STILL LOVE
MY MATERIAL GIRL!

15:15.917 --> 15:18.208
[ LAUGHS ]

15:18.291 --> 15:20.291
[ SIGHS ]

15:22.417 --> 15:24.583
YOU'RE BACK.

15:24.667 --> 15:28.333
UH, JUST CHECKING IN.
I DIDN'T MEAN TO DISTURB YOU.

15:28.417 --> 15:30.250
NO, NOT DISTURBING ME
AT ALL.

15:30.333 --> 15:32.542
CHARLIE'S RESTING.

15:32.625 --> 15:34.041
WHAT'S THE PROGNOSIS?

15:34.125 --> 15:35.166
ANY CHANCE HE'LL BE
MOVING HIS INDEX FINGER

15:35.250 --> 15:36.583
BEFORE
THE END OF THE DAY?

15:36.667 --> 15:40.417
IT'S IMPORTANT
NOT TO RUSH PROGRESS.

15:40.500 --> 15:42.083
IT'S GONNA TAKE TIME

15:42.166 --> 15:44.709
FOR THE BRAIN TO WAKE UP
AND FIND ALTERNATE PATHWAYS,

15:44.792 --> 15:47.959
ESPECIALLY WHEN THINGS HAVE BEEN
THE SAME WAY FOR SO LONG.

15:48.041 --> 15:51.333
IT'S RATHER LIKE GETTING BACK
INTO A RELATIONSHIP

15:51.417 --> 15:54.667
WHEN YOU'VE BEEN SINGLE
FOR A WHILE, AS <i>I</i> HAVE.

15:55.917 --> 15:57.834
OH?

15:57.917 --> 16:00.750
<i>HE MAY BE A GENIUS,</i>
<i>BUT THE DUDE IS</i> NOT <i>SUBTLE.</i>

16:00.834 --> 16:02.583
WELL...
[ SIGHS ]

16:02.667 --> 16:05.500
FOR INSTANCE [CHUCKLES]
ASKING SOMEONE OUT TO DINNER,

16:05.583 --> 16:08.041
UH, SHOULD BE EASY --

16:08.125 --> 16:10.041
JUST AS MOVING A FINGER
SHOULD BE EASY,

16:10.125 --> 16:14.667
UH, E-EXCEPT
WHEN IT'S...NOT.

16:14.750 --> 16:18.333
WELL,
YOU'RE THE DOCTOR.

16:18.417 --> 16:20.500
WHATEVER YOU THINK
IS BEST.

16:20.583 --> 16:22.667
FOR CHARLIE.

16:22.750 --> 16:25.834
<i>YEAH. 'CAUSE</i> THAT'S <i>WHAT</i>
<i>WE WERE TALKING ABOUT.</i>

16:29.500 --> 16:31.834
[ SIGHS ]

16:34.542 --> 16:36.583
KARA!

16:36.667 --> 16:38.417
I'M SO GLAD YOU TEXTED.
NOT GONNA LIE,

16:38.500 --> 16:40.583
IT <i>WAS</i> A LITTLE HARD
TO BREAK INTO YOUR ROOM,

16:40.667 --> 16:42.625
THIRD FLOOR AND ALL,
BUT MISSION ACCOMPLISHED.

16:42.709 --> 16:44.083
YOUR CHARIOT AWAITS.

16:44.166 --> 16:45.500
WELL DONE.

16:45.583 --> 16:47.125
SO, WHERE ARE WE HEADED?
WHAT'S THE PLAN?

16:47.208 --> 16:48.709
[ ENGINE TURNS OVER ]
WANT TO GROVE IT UP?

16:48.792 --> 16:50.458
[ TIRES SQUEAL ]
OKAY, UH...

16:50.542 --> 16:53.208
I'LL JUST MEET UP
WITH YOU GUYS LATER!

16:53.291 --> 16:54.917
Leo: ALL RIGHT,
SO, TO GET TO EMMA'S,

16:55.000 --> 16:57.083
WE NEED TO HOP ON THE FREEWAY,
UH, WHICH IS <i>THAT</i> WAY.

16:57.166 --> 16:58.834
KARA, THE FREE--
THE FREEWAY'S THAT WAY.

16:58.917 --> 17:01.208
YEAH, WE'RE NOT GOING
TO EMMA'S HOUSE.

17:04.083 --> 17:05.709
[ SIGHS ]

17:09.000 --> 17:10.375
[ WHISTLE BLOWS ]

17:10.458 --> 17:12.959
♪ GOODBYE TO
MY SANTA MONICA DREAM ♪

17:13.041 --> 17:16.125
Cheerleaders: GO, GO, G-O!
GO, VIKINGS, GO!

17:16.208 --> 17:20.542
♪ 15 KIDS IN THE BACKYARD
DRINKING WINE ♪

17:20.625 --> 17:23.125
GO, GO, G-O!

17:23.208 --> 17:28.834
♪ YOU TELL ME STORIES
OF THE SEA ♪

17:28.917 --> 17:32.333
YOU GONNA GO AND SAY HI
TO YOUR FRIENDS AT SOME POINT?

17:32.417 --> 17:33.834
THEY AREN'T
MY FRIENDS ANYMORE.

17:33.917 --> 17:36.291
OKAY, THEN WHAT
ARE WE DOING HERE?

17:36.375 --> 17:39.333
WATCHING THE WORLD
SPIN MADLY ON WITHOUT US.

17:39.417 --> 17:41.000
[ CHEERING ]
HEY, YOU'RE GONNA BE
BACK OUT THERE

17:41.083 --> 17:42.959
BEFORE YOU KNOW IT.
DON'T WORRY.

17:43.041 --> 17:44.959
I'M NEVER GOING BACK
TO THIS SCHOOL,

17:45.041 --> 17:47.333
EVEN WHEN I LEAVE THE
HOSPITAL -- <i>IF</i> I LEAVE.

17:47.417 --> 17:49.041
OF COURSE
YOU'RE GONNA LEAVE.

17:49.125 --> 17:50.375
UNLESS I DIE THERE.

17:50.458 --> 17:51.792
WHAT IS WRONG WITH YOU?

17:51.875 --> 17:52.875
DID THEY SWITCH YOUR MEDS
OR SOMETHING?

17:52.959 --> 17:54.375
WHAT DO YOU CARE?

17:54.458 --> 17:55.875
I DON'T, BUT SINCE YOU DRAGGED
ME OUT HERE --

17:55.959 --> 17:57.625
NO, I NEVER INVITED YOU.
YOU CRASHED THIS PARTY.

17:57.709 --> 17:59.291
SOME PARTY.

17:59.375 --> 18:01.083
LOOK, IF YOU DON'T
WANT TO COME BACK HERE,

18:01.166 --> 18:03.000
YOU CAN ALWAYS TRANSFER
TO A DIFFERENT SCHOOL,

18:03.083 --> 18:04.458
RESUME
YOUR REIGN OF TERROR

18:04.542 --> 18:06.125
ON A NEW PACK OF
UNSUSPECTING CHEERLEADERS.

18:06.208 --> 18:07.792
NOT INTERESTED.
REALLY?

18:07.875 --> 18:09.792
REALLY.

18:09.875 --> 18:12.458
I JUST DON'T THINK I HAVE IT
IN ME ANYMORE.

18:14.083 --> 18:16.083
[ SCOFFS ]

18:16.166 --> 18:19.583
GOD, I'M NOT INTERESTED
IN <i>ANYTHING</i> ANYMORE.

18:19.667 --> 18:21.834
WELL, EXCEPT HUNTER.

18:23.834 --> 18:29.083
FOR WHAT IT'S WORTH,
I KNOW EXACTLY HOW YOU FEEL.

18:29.166 --> 18:30.792
I HAVE NO IDEA
WHAT I'M GONNA DO

18:30.875 --> 18:32.417
WHEN I GET OUT
OF THE HOSPITAL.

18:32.500 --> 18:34.000
OH, MY GOD.

18:34.083 --> 18:36.083
WHAT, I'M NOT ALLOWED TO HAVE
AN EXISTENTIAL CRISIS?

18:36.166 --> 18:38.083
NO, YOU'RE NOT.
WHY NOT?

18:38.166 --> 18:41.125
'CAUSE IT'S SO PAINFULLY OBVIOUS
WHAT YOU'RE GONNA DO.

18:41.208 --> 18:42.792
EVERYONE
KNOWS IT BUT YOU.

18:42.875 --> 18:45.792
AS USUAL, I HAVE NO IDEA
WHAT YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT.

18:45.875 --> 18:48.834
COME ON. I'LL SHOW YOU.
WHERE ARE WE GOING NOW?

18:48.917 --> 18:50.417
NOT TELLING.

18:50.500 --> 18:52.291
THIS IS STARTING TO BECOME
A THING WITH YOU.

18:52.375 --> 18:55.166
[ WHISTLE BLOWS ]
[ CHEERLEADERS CHEER ]

18:58.500 --> 19:00.750
YOU OKAY, DR. NADAY?

19:00.834 --> 19:02.083
YEAH,
COULDN'T BE BETTER.

19:02.166 --> 19:03.750
WOULD YOU LIKE ME
TO GRAB A MAGAZINE

19:03.834 --> 19:05.375
OR SOMETHING TO READ
WHILE YOU EAT?

19:05.458 --> 19:06.959
[ Chuckling ]
OH, NO, NO, I'M FINE.

19:07.041 --> 19:08.458
THANKS.

19:08.542 --> 19:09.792
AT LUNCH,
I LIKE TO TAKE A BREAK --

19:09.875 --> 19:11.125
A-A <i>REAL</i> BREAK.

19:11.208 --> 19:13.709
I LIKE TO CLEANSE THE PALATE
OF THE MIND.

19:15.041 --> 19:17.542
DO I LOOK STRANGE?

19:17.625 --> 19:20.375
HEY, IF IT DOESN'T BOTHER YOU,
IT DOESN'T BOTHER ME.
[ CHUCKLES ]

19:20.458 --> 19:22.667
BUT I'M BEGINNING TO UNDERSTAND
WHY YOU'RE SINGLE.

19:22.750 --> 19:24.291
[ CHUCKLES ]

19:24.375 --> 19:26.750
THEN AGAIN, I'VE BEEN SINGLE
FOR A WHILE MYSELF, SO...

19:26.834 --> 19:28.542
IT'S EASY
TO GET STUCK IN A RUT.

19:28.625 --> 19:30.625
WELL, IF YOU'RE WORRIED ABOUT
MY REPUTATION AROUND HERE,

19:30.709 --> 19:32.125
YOU --
YOU COULD JOIN ME.

19:32.208 --> 19:34.291
OH, NO, NO. I LIKE TO BRING
MY LUNCH FROM HOME.

19:34.375 --> 19:35.667
I LIKE TO COOK.

19:35.750 --> 19:37.250
AND I LIKE
BUYING COOKBOOKS,

19:37.333 --> 19:39.750
JUST HAVEN'T GRADUATED
TO THE NEXT LEVEL YET.

19:39.834 --> 19:41.250
YOU SHOULD
COME OVER SOMETIME.

19:41.333 --> 19:43.125
A HOME-COOKED MEAL
IS VERY IMPORTANT --

19:43.208 --> 19:45.625
I'D LOVE TO.

19:45.709 --> 19:49.291
OKAY, THEN.

19:49.375 --> 19:51.375
I-IT'S A...DATE.

19:51.458 --> 19:53.125
GREAT.

19:53.208 --> 19:56.667
UH, HEY, DAD,
CAN I TALK TO YOU FOR A SECOND?

19:56.750 --> 19:59.291
SURE THING.
WHAT'S UP?

19:59.375 --> 20:02.166
IT'S ABOUT GRANDMA.
UM, MOM SAID SOMETHING EARLIER.

20:02.250 --> 20:03.542
[ SIGHS ]

20:03.625 --> 20:06.834
SWEETIE, THIS IS
A LARGER CONVERSATION.

20:06.917 --> 20:09.625
WE SHOULD WAIT UNTIL YOUR MOM
GETS BACK FROM THE MARKET.

20:09.709 --> 20:12.917
COME ON, DAD.
TALK TO ME.

20:16.458 --> 20:18.375
WE THINK IT'S...

20:18.458 --> 20:21.709
POSSIBLE
YOUR GRANDMOTHER...

20:21.792 --> 20:24.542
MAY HAVE SUFFERED
FROM SIMILAR...

20:24.625 --> 20:25.959
[ SIGHS ]

20:26.041 --> 20:30.750
YOU THINK THAT GRANDMA
WAS ANOREXIC?

20:30.834 --> 20:34.417
YOUR GRANDMOTHER WAS ALWAYS VERY
CONSCIOUS OF HER WEIGHT AND...

20:34.500 --> 20:37.083
SKINNY SINCE THE DAY
I MET HER.

20:37.166 --> 20:39.583
BUT I DON'T THINK IT WOULD HAVE
EVER OCCURRED TO ME

20:39.667 --> 20:41.291
UNTIL SHE PASSED AWAY.

20:41.375 --> 20:43.083
WHY?
W-WHAT HAPPENED THEN?

20:43.166 --> 20:48.125
WELL, YOUR MOTHER AND I WENT TO
CLEAN OUT GRANDMA'S APARTMENT.

20:48.208 --> 20:51.375
AND WHEN WE WERE GOING
THROUGH HER THINGS...

20:53.959 --> 20:58.875
...WE FOUND OLD FOOD
HIDDEN AWAY EVERYWHERE.

20:58.959 --> 21:01.542
SANDWICHES
SHE'D NEVER EATEN.

21:01.625 --> 21:04.875
UNTOUCHED CANDY,
STALE CUPCAKES.

21:04.959 --> 21:07.875
IT INDICATED
A LARGER PROBLEM

21:07.959 --> 21:10.375
AND, IN RETROSPECT, A LOT OF
THINGS STARTED TO MAKE SENSE.

21:10.458 --> 21:14.667
HOW, UM -- HOW COULD YOU NOT
TELL ME ABOUT THIS BEFORE NOW?

21:17.625 --> 21:19.000
WE TALKED ABOUT IT.

21:19.083 --> 21:22.542
DAD, I HAVE FELT SO ALONE
FOR SO LONG.

21:22.625 --> 21:24.583
I DIDN'T KNOW WHY THIS WAS
HAPPENING TO ME.

21:24.667 --> 21:26.542
AND ALL THIS TIME,
THERE'S BEEN A REASON.

21:26.625 --> 21:28.125
Caroline:
THERE'S NO REASON.

21:29.542 --> 21:31.750
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING
ABOUT, MOM?

21:31.834 --> 21:34.125
ANOREXIA IS A DISEASE.

21:34.208 --> 21:36.291
JUST LIKE ALCOHOLISM
OR DRUG ADDICTION,

21:36.375 --> 21:37.959
THERE'S
A GENETIC COMPONENT.

21:38.041 --> 21:40.625
WHY WOULD YOU KEEP SOMETHING
LIKE THIS FROM ME?

21:40.709 --> 21:43.166
BECAUSE I WASN'T ABOUT TO GIVE
YOU PERMISSION TO BE DAMAGED.

21:43.250 --> 21:44.625
WHAT?!
CAROLINE --

21:44.709 --> 21:45.959
AS SOON AS YOU IDENTIFY THIS
AS A DISEASE,

21:46.041 --> 21:47.542
SOMETHING
YOU WERE BORN WITH,

21:47.625 --> 21:49.875
IT MAKES YOU LESS LIKELY
TO TRY AND CHANGE IT.

21:49.959 --> 21:51.959
YOU START TO THINK
IT'S OUT OF YOUR CONTROL.

21:52.041 --> 21:53.625
I DON'T BELIEVE THIS.

21:53.709 --> 21:55.583
HONEY, YOU'RE UPSET NOW.
BUT ONE DAY, YOU'LL UNDERSTAND.

21:55.667 --> 21:57.583
HONEY --
NO, I WILL <i>NEVER</i>
UNDERSTAND YOU, MOM!

21:57.667 --> 21:59.083
I HATE YOU!

21:59.166 --> 22:00.417
WHAT --

22:00.500 --> 22:02.500
EMMA.
[ STAMMERS ]

22:04.917 --> 22:06.500
[ P.A. BEEPS ]

22:06.583 --> 22:09.417
Woman: <i>PAGING DR. NADAY.</i>
<i>LINE SEVEN, PLEASE.</i>

22:09.500 --> 22:11.125
I'LL MEET YOU GUYS
OUTSIDE?

22:11.208 --> 22:14.250
YEAH,
WE'LL PULL THE CAR OUT.

22:14.333 --> 22:15.917
HEY, HUNTER.

22:17.125 --> 22:18.500
SAFE DRIVE HOME.

22:18.583 --> 22:21.041
STAY OUT OF TROUBLE.

22:21.125 --> 22:23.208
I'LL DO MY BEST.

22:23.291 --> 22:25.583
IT WAS NICE
MEETING YOU, MAN.
YOU TOO.

22:25.667 --> 22:26.834
FIGHT THE GOOD FIGHT.

22:26.917 --> 22:28.750
YO, MAN,
TRIED TO CALL KARA,

22:28.834 --> 22:30.500
BUT SHE WOULD NOT
PICK UP HER PHONE.

22:30.583 --> 22:32.125
OH, IT'S OKAY.

22:32.208 --> 22:33.375
I HAVE A FEELING KARA ISN'T BIG
ON GOODBYES --

22:33.458 --> 22:35.250
ANOTHER THING
WE HAVE IN COMMON.

22:35.333 --> 22:37.291
YEAH, SHE'S NOT THAT GREAT WITH
SAYING "HELLO" EITHER, BUT...

22:37.375 --> 22:39.208
[ LAUGHS ]
...YOU HAD HER
ALL TURNED AROUND.

22:39.291 --> 22:41.125
SHE'S GONNA BE ALL ADRIFT
NOW THAT YOU'RE GONE, MAN.

22:41.208 --> 22:42.875
GOOD THING
SHE'S GOT YOU GUYS.

22:42.959 --> 22:44.208
[ BEEPING ]
[ P.A. BEEPS ]

22:44.291 --> 22:46.125
[ INDISTINCT TALKING OVER P.A. ]

22:46.208 --> 22:47.125
WELL, SEE YOU MAYBE.

22:47.208 --> 22:48.208
SEE YOU MAYBE.

22:48.291 --> 22:50.208
[ BEEPING CONTINUES ]

22:50.291 --> 22:51.959
WHAT IS THAT?

22:55.417 --> 22:56.834
OH, MY GOD.
WHAT THE HELL?

22:56.917 --> 22:58.500
WHAT'S GOING ON?

22:58.583 --> 22:59.875
IT'S MY UNOS PAGER.

22:59.959 --> 23:01.542
WHAT'S THAT MEAN?
THAT MEANS THAT HOMEBOY

23:01.625 --> 23:03.667
IS NOT GOING ANYWHERE!

23:03.750 --> 23:05.792
NEW LIVER FLYING IN,
PEOPLE!

23:05.875 --> 23:07.542
NEW LIVER!

23:07.625 --> 23:09.500
THAT'S A GOOD THING!

23:09.583 --> 23:11.834
OH, MY GOD!

23:11.917 --> 23:13.208
♪ OOH-OOH, OOH-OOH ♪

23:15.750 --> 23:17.000
E.T.A.
ON HUNTER'S LIVER?

23:17.083 --> 23:18.792
FLYING IN
FROM SACRAMENTO NOW.

23:18.875 --> 23:20.083
HUNTER'S BEING PREPPED,

23:20.166 --> 23:23.000
AND DR. KING
IS ON HIS WAY.

23:26.875 --> 23:31.500
ANYBODY HAVE ANYTHING ELSE
THEY WANT TO TALK ABOUT?

23:33.291 --> 23:35.709
HUH.

23:35.792 --> 23:37.709
THAT'S FINE.

23:37.792 --> 23:39.917
PERHAPS NOW WOULD BE A GOOD TIME
FOR ME TO PERFORM

23:40.000 --> 23:42.000
A MOVING RENDITION
OF "PAPA, CAN YOU HEAR ME?"

23:42.083 --> 23:43.041
I SLEPT WITH McANDREW.

23:43.125 --> 23:44.709
YOU WHAT?!            YOU WHAT?!

23:44.792 --> 23:46.583
UNH-UNH, ME FIRST.
HAVE YOU LOST YOUR DAMN MIND?

23:46.667 --> 23:47.834
APPARENTLY.

23:47.917 --> 23:49.291
BUT WHEN? HOW?
WAS IT GOOD?

23:49.375 --> 23:51.083
NOPE, NOT EVEN ASKING THAT.
YOU'RE NO FUN.

23:51.166 --> 23:52.750
SERIOUSLY, WHAT WERE YOU
THINKING, BRITTANY?

23:52.834 --> 23:54.583
I-I WAS THINKING HE LIKED ME,
AND I LIKED HIM,

23:54.667 --> 23:57.291
A-AND WE HAD
THIS BACK-AND-FORTH THING

23:57.375 --> 23:59.625
GOING ON FOR A WHILE
WITH GRANOLA BARS

23:59.709 --> 24:01.959
AND OTHER STUFF, AND...

24:02.041 --> 24:03.834
I LIKED HIM.

24:03.917 --> 24:05.500
SO...

24:05.583 --> 24:07.417
WHAT'S HAPPENING NOW?
ARE YOU TWO DATING, WHAT?

24:07.500 --> 24:10.083
[ SCOFFS ]
NO, NOTHING'S HAPPENING.

24:10.166 --> 24:13.709
IT HAPPENED, AND...
IT'S OVER.

24:13.792 --> 24:15.208
WELL, THAT EXPLAINS
THE WEIRDNESS.

24:15.291 --> 24:16.875
WHAT WEIRDNESS?
THERE'S BEEN WEIRDNESS.

24:16.959 --> 24:17.875
[ SIGHS ]

24:17.959 --> 24:19.542
AM I CRAZY?

24:19.625 --> 24:21.291
I MEAN, DIDN'T IT SEEM LIKE
HE WAS KIND OF INTO ME, TOO?

24:21.375 --> 24:22.959
YEAH.
BUT THAT'S NOT THE POINT.

24:23.041 --> 24:25.500
YOU KNOW AS WELL AS I DO
OFFICE ROMANCES NEVER WORK.

24:25.583 --> 24:27.333
BUT --
PAM AND JIM ARE FAKE.

24:27.417 --> 24:29.792
FAKE!

24:29.875 --> 24:32.792
ALL RIGHT, WHAT THESE SCANS
INDICATE IS A PARTIAL RESPONSE.

24:32.875 --> 24:36.000
YOUR --
YOUR TUMORS HAVE SHRUNK,

24:36.083 --> 24:38.667
BUT NOT AS SIGNIFICANTLY
AS WE WOULD HAVE HOPED FOR.

24:38.750 --> 24:40.166
WELL, THAT SUCKS.

24:40.250 --> 24:44.208
IT DOESN'T SUCK AS MUCH
AS IT COULD HAVE SUCKED.

24:44.291 --> 24:47.208
NOW, LOOK,
IT'S MY JOB TO INFORM YOU

24:47.291 --> 24:49.583
THAT ATTEMPTING TO
SURGICALLY REMOVE TUMORS

24:49.667 --> 24:53.250
THAT ARE THAT INVASIVE
WOULD BE CONSIDERED RISKY.

24:53.333 --> 24:54.959
MOST DOCTORS
WOULD PROBABLY SUGGEST

24:55.041 --> 24:57.250
THAT YOU GO THROUGH
ANOTHER CYCLE OF CHEMOTHERAPY.

24:57.333 --> 25:00.125
OH.

25:00.208 --> 25:02.208
BUT...
I'M NOT MOST DOCTORS.

25:02.291 --> 25:04.166
I'VE HANDLED
TUMORS THIS SIZE BEFORE.

25:04.250 --> 25:06.500
AND IF YOU'RE UP FOR IT,
I WANT TO GO BACK IN.

25:06.583 --> 25:08.041
BUT I WANT YOU TO THINK
ABOUT IT.

25:08.125 --> 25:09.959
I WANT YOU TO TALK
TO SOME OTHERS DOCTORS HERE.

25:10.041 --> 25:11.291
I DON'T NEED
TO TALK TO ANYONE.

25:11.375 --> 25:12.875
YOU'RE MY DOCTOR.

25:12.959 --> 25:15.875
I TRUST YOU.

25:15.959 --> 25:17.625
ALL RIGHT.

25:17.709 --> 25:19.375
I'LL SEE IF I CAN GET THIS
ON THE SCHEDULE FOR TOMORROW.

25:19.458 --> 25:20.875
TOMORROW?

25:20.959 --> 25:22.375
DO YOU HAVE PLANS?

25:22.458 --> 25:23.750
I DO NOW.

25:23.834 --> 25:27.291
THANK YOU SO MUCH.

25:29.333 --> 25:32.750
WHO KNOWS?
MAYBE I'LL BE NEXT.

25:32.834 --> 25:34.166
NEXT FOR WHAT?

25:34.250 --> 25:38.500
NEXT TO GO HOME.

25:38.583 --> 25:41.834
THIS WAS ODDLY DIFFICULT
TO FIND.

25:41.917 --> 25:44.709
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

25:45.959 --> 25:48.333
REMINDING YOU
WHO YOU ARE.

25:48.417 --> 25:50.333
I'M NOT PLAYING SOCCER
ANYMORE, KARA.

25:50.417 --> 25:52.166
I MADE THAT DECISION
A WHILE AGO.

25:52.250 --> 25:53.458
IT WAS <i>YOUR</i> DOING MOSTLY.

25:53.542 --> 25:54.834
JUST KICK THE BALL,
DUDE.

25:54.917 --> 25:56.917
THANKS,
BUT NO, THANKS.

25:57.000 --> 25:58.875
I WILL TAKE
YOUR TRANSFORMER LEG

25:58.959 --> 26:00.959
AND BASH IT
INTO YOUR PATCHY SKULL.

26:01.041 --> 26:03.333
[ SIGHS ]
NOW KICK THE DAMN BALL.

26:04.917 --> 26:07.333
HAVE YOU EVER CONSIDERED BEING
A MOTIVATIONAL SPEAKER?

26:07.417 --> 26:08.542
IT COULD
BE YOUR CALLING.

26:10.458 --> 26:11.667
OKAY, MOVE.

26:19.125 --> 26:22.875
♪ AND AFTER ALL ♪

26:22.959 --> 26:23.917
♪ THESE TIMES ♪

26:24.000 --> 26:26.291
[ LAUGHS ]

26:26.375 --> 26:28.792
SO?

26:28.875 --> 26:30.458
HOW DID THAT FEEL?

26:30.542 --> 26:31.959
[ SIGHS ]

26:32.041 --> 26:34.208
AWESOME, ACTUALLY.

26:34.291 --> 26:35.792
NOW, I WANT YOU
TO PROMISE ME SOMETHING.

26:35.875 --> 26:37.542
WHAT IS IT?

26:37.625 --> 26:38.875
WHEN YOU GO HOME,

26:38.959 --> 26:40.917
I WANT YOU TO FORGET
ABOUT ALL OF US.

26:41.000 --> 26:42.083
ESPECIALLY HER.

26:42.166 --> 26:43.959
JUST GO HOME
AND NEVER LOOK BACK.

26:44.041 --> 26:46.792
OKAY?

26:46.875 --> 26:48.291
I'M SORRY, KARA.

26:48.375 --> 26:50.625
I DON'T THINK
THAT'S GONNA BE POSSIBLE.

26:50.709 --> 26:51.959
WHY NOT?

26:52.041 --> 26:54.458
'CAUSE HOW COULD
ANYBODY EVER FORGET YOU?

26:54.542 --> 26:57.375
♪ OH, OH, OH ♪

27:02.917 --> 27:05.917
[ CRICKETS CHIRPING ]

27:14.208 --> 27:17.458
LEO: <i>Hey, Emma.</i>
<i>It's me.</i>

27:17.542 --> 27:19.125
<i>I was hoping you'd pick up,</i>

27:19.208 --> 27:21.625
<i>but you're probably</i>
<i>getting settled in.</i>

27:21.709 --> 27:24.959
<i>Or maybe</i>
<i>you're still mad at me.</i>

27:25.041 --> 27:28.792
<i>I hope not.</i>

27:28.875 --> 27:31.792
<i>I'm sorry, Emma.</i>

27:31.875 --> 27:33.959
<i>I feel like an idiot</i>

27:34.041 --> 27:36.458
<i>for not understanding</i>
<i>what was going on with you.</i>

27:36.542 --> 27:38.125
<i>And for making you feel</i>

27:38.208 --> 27:40.083
<i>like you had to be something</i>
<i>you're not.</i>

27:40.166 --> 27:43.458
<i>That's the last thing I wanted.</i>
<i>Anyway, I'm rambling now.</i>

27:43.542 --> 27:45.417
<i>Call me when you get this.</i>

27:45.500 --> 27:47.792
<i>I just want to hear your voice,</i>
<i>make sure y-you're, uh...</i>

27:47.875 --> 27:49.125
<i>You're okay.</i>

27:49.208 --> 27:52.417
<i>Emma, I-I-I...</i>
<i>I miss you.</i>

27:54.542 --> 27:55.458
[ SNIFFLES ]

27:55.542 --> 27:57.458
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

27:57.542 --> 27:58.959
Finley: IT'S JUST ME.

27:59.041 --> 28:00.417
COME IN.

28:00.500 --> 28:02.583
HEY, EMMA, SH--

28:02.667 --> 28:04.000
ARE YOU OKAY?

28:04.083 --> 28:06.166
YEAH, I'M FINE.

28:06.250 --> 28:08.500
MOM WANTS YOU TO HELP SET
THE TABLE FOR DINNER.

28:08.583 --> 28:09.667
OH, I'M NOT HUNGRY.

28:09.750 --> 28:11.959
YOU <i>HAVE</i> TO EAT.

28:12.041 --> 28:14.625
I KNOW.

28:14.709 --> 28:17.291
I'M SORRY.

28:17.375 --> 28:20.417
IT'S OKAY.

28:20.500 --> 28:23.250
NO, FINN,
IT'S NOT OKAY.

28:23.333 --> 28:25.875
I NEVER THOUGHT ABOUT HOW
ALL THIS WAS AFFECTING YOU.

28:25.959 --> 28:29.500
ARE YOU REALLY BETTER?

28:31.709 --> 28:33.709
TRYING TO BE.

28:35.542 --> 28:37.542
[ SIREN WAILING IN DISTANCE ]

28:41.875 --> 28:44.291
WHAT ARE
<i>YOU</i> DOING HERE?

28:44.375 --> 28:46.625
[ SIGHS ] WE'RE LOW
ON RED BAND RESERVES,

28:46.709 --> 28:48.792
BUT NO ONE GOES UNDER THE KNIFE
WITHOUT A PEP TALK,

28:48.875 --> 28:50.291
NOT ON MY WATCH.

28:50.375 --> 28:52.458
YOU TAKE THIS STUFF
PRETTY SERIOUSLY, DON'T YOU?

28:52.542 --> 28:54.041
I DO.

28:54.125 --> 28:55.458
YOU KNOW,
WHEN I FIRST MET YOU,

28:55.542 --> 28:57.041
I THOUGHT YOU WERE
KIND OF A POSER.

28:57.125 --> 28:58.542
KETTLE, BLACK.

28:58.625 --> 29:00.500
BUT I THINK I UNDERESTIMATED
YOUR LEADERSHIP,

29:00.583 --> 29:02.709
MAYBE BECAUSE
<i>YOU</i> UNDERESTIMATE IT.

29:02.792 --> 29:04.709
YOU WALK AROUND
LIKE A NUMBER TWO,

29:04.792 --> 29:06.709
CHIEF OF STAFF
TO PRESIDENT LEO.

29:06.792 --> 29:10.375
BUT I THINK
YOU'VE GOT IT BACKWARDS.

29:10.458 --> 29:12.750
FROM WHERE I SIT,

29:12.834 --> 29:16.250
YOU'RE THE ONE HOLDING THINGS
TOGETHER AROUND HERE.

29:16.333 --> 29:19.208
Kenji: HUNTER, I'M GONNA TAKE
YOU UPSTAIRS NOW.

29:19.291 --> 29:20.834
I'M JUST
GONNA GRAB A CHAIR.

29:29.166 --> 29:31.250
IF I DON'T WAKE UP,

29:31.333 --> 29:33.917
WOULD YOU MIND GIVING THIS
TO KARA FOR ME?

29:34.000 --> 29:36.834
YOU CAN GIVE IT
TO HER YOURSELF.

29:48.000 --> 29:50.000
THANKS, DASH.

29:53.667 --> 29:57.375
CATCH YOU
ON THE FLIP SIDE.

30:04.875 --> 30:07.291
SO, WHAT TIME'S YOUR GAME
THIS SATURDAY, FINLEY?

30:07.375 --> 30:08.625
3:00,
BUT WE'RE PLAYING LINCOLN,

30:08.709 --> 30:10.291
SO WE'RE TOTALLY
GONNA GET DESTROYED.

30:10.375 --> 30:13.792
OH, YOU WILL
IF YOU KEEP UP <i>THAT</i> ATTITUDE.

30:13.875 --> 30:15.667
HEY, DO YOU WANT TO PRACTICE
YOUR SERVE AFTER DINNER?

30:15.750 --> 30:17.125
SURE.

30:17.208 --> 30:19.125
MAYBE EMMA COULD GIVE YOU
A FEW POINTERS.

30:19.208 --> 30:20.625
YOU WERE ALWAYS GREAT
AT VOLLEYBALL.

30:20.709 --> 30:22.250
HAVEN'T PLAYED IN YEARS.

30:22.333 --> 30:24.500
WELL,
IT'LL COME BACK TO YOU.

30:26.792 --> 30:29.375
YOU'RE NOT LEAVING UNTIL
YOU CLEAN YOUR PLATE, EMMA.

30:29.458 --> 30:31.041
CAROLINE --

30:31.125 --> 30:33.041
I SPOKE TO YOUR DOCTORS,
AND I HAVEN'T GIVEN YOU ANY MORE

30:33.125 --> 30:34.500
THAN WHAT YOU'RE
USED TO EATING THERE.

30:34.583 --> 30:35.792
MOM,
THIS IS A LOT MORE.

30:35.875 --> 30:37.333
WE CAN
CALL THEM RIGHT NOW.

30:37.417 --> 30:39.083
MAY I PLEASE BE EXCUSED?
[ UTENSIL CLATTERS ]

30:39.166 --> 30:41.542
NO. THIS IS OUR FIRST
FAMILY DINNER IN A LONG TIME,

30:41.625 --> 30:43.250
AND WE ARE ALL
GOING TO SIT TOGETHER...

30:43.333 --> 30:46.291
AND EAT.

30:46.375 --> 30:49.291
LIKE A FAMILY.

30:49.375 --> 30:51.792
PLEASE, EMMA.

30:51.875 --> 30:54.291
TRY.

30:54.375 --> 30:56.542
SURE.
[ CHUCKLES LIGHTLY ]

31:12.000 --> 31:15.667
NO, NO, T-THAT MAKES
NO SENSE WHATSOEVER.

31:15.750 --> 31:18.375
I DON'T HAVE TIME
TO APPEAL YOUR DECISION.

31:18.458 --> 31:20.250
WHATEVER
COURSE OF TREATMENT

31:20.333 --> 31:25.709
WE DECIDE WE'RE TAKING NEEDS
TO BE IMPLEMENTED NOW, TODAY!

31:25.792 --> 31:27.709
OH, DO NOT GIVE ME
THAT BUREAUCRATIC CRAP.

31:27.792 --> 31:29.583
JUST DON'T --
[ Click ]

31:29.667 --> 31:32.583
[ Scoffing ]
OH, THAT'S PERFECT.

31:32.667 --> 31:33.875
[ SIGHS ]

31:37.750 --> 31:40.583
SORRY.
YOU SHOULD BE.

31:42.166 --> 31:43.917
BRITTANY,
SNAP OUT OF IT.

31:44.000 --> 31:45.208
EXCUSE ME?

31:45.291 --> 31:46.625
IF I HURT YOUR FEELINGS

31:46.709 --> 31:48.417
OR I MISLED YOU IN ANY WAY,
I APOLOGIZE,

31:48.500 --> 31:50.667
BUT THIS IS A HOSPITAL,
AND CHILDREN ARE SICK.

31:50.750 --> 31:52.500
SO WHATEVER'S GOING ON
IN OUR PERSONAL LIFE

31:52.583 --> 31:55.083
SEEMS PRETTY RIDICULOUS
BY COMPARISON, RIGHT?

31:55.166 --> 31:57.166
SO EITHER GET OVER IT
OR GET OUT.

32:08.959 --> 32:10.375
ALL DONE?

32:10.458 --> 32:12.041
JUST ONE
LAST GAME OF DRAUGHTS

32:12.125 --> 32:13.375
BEFORE I HEAD BACK
TO MY HOTEL.

32:13.458 --> 32:14.917
DRAUGHTS?

32:15.000 --> 32:16.709
SORRY.
YOU GUYS CALL IT "CHECKERS."
MM.

32:16.792 --> 32:19.875
I WAS BEGINNING TO THINK THAT
CHESS MAY BE TOO COMPLICATED.

32:19.959 --> 32:22.875
ACTUALLY, MY HOTEL
IS JUST AROUND THE CORNER.

32:22.959 --> 32:24.125
YOU WOULDN'T LIKE
TO JOIN ME FOR DRINKS

32:24.208 --> 32:25.667
AFTER YOUR SHIFT,
WOULD YOU?

32:25.750 --> 32:27.959
WE COULD DISCUSS THE MENU
FOR OUR UPCOMING DINNER.

32:28.041 --> 32:29.959
UH...

32:30.041 --> 32:32.125
SORRY,
I-I-I CAN'T TONIGHT.

32:32.208 --> 32:34.625
OH, OF COURSE.
I UNDERSTAND.

32:34.709 --> 32:37.583
ACTUALLY, UH...

32:37.667 --> 32:39.250
I-I...

32:39.333 --> 32:41.625
HAVE A <i>LOT</i>
GOING ON RIGHT NOW.

32:41.709 --> 32:43.625
I-IT'S KIND
OF A-A BAD TIME.

32:43.709 --> 32:45.417
I-I DON'T...

32:45.500 --> 32:48.583
I DON'T KNOW WHAT I WAS THINKING
THIS AFTERNOON.

32:48.667 --> 32:52.166
REALLY SHOULDN'T HAVE OFFERED
TO COOK FOR YOU.

32:54.834 --> 32:57.250
WELL,
IF YOU'RE BUSY...

32:57.333 --> 33:01.000
YOU'RE --
YOU'RE BUSY.

33:02.917 --> 33:05.959
HAVE A GOOD NIGHT.

33:06.041 --> 33:09.375
YOU TOO.

33:27.667 --> 33:29.083
YOU COMING?

33:29.166 --> 33:31.750
NOT YET.
YOU CAN GO IN.

33:31.834 --> 33:33.917
I'M IN NO RUSH.

33:34.000 --> 33:36.250
[ SIGHS ]

33:36.333 --> 33:37.834
I CAN'T BELIEVE
NURSE JACKSON

33:37.917 --> 33:39.792
HASN'T SENT A S.W.A.T. TEAM
AFTER US BY NOW.

33:39.875 --> 33:42.625
I'VE BEEN UPDATING HER ALL DAY.
SHE KNOWS WE'RE FINE.

33:42.709 --> 33:44.458
YOU'VE BEEN...

33:44.542 --> 33:46.458
[ SCOFFS ]

33:46.542 --> 33:50.125
GOD, YOU JUST CAN'T HELP
BUT BE GOOD, CAN YOU?

33:50.208 --> 33:53.166
MUST BE IN MY DNA.

33:53.250 --> 33:56.166
HEY, DO YOU WANT TO
TALK ABOUT IT YET?

33:56.250 --> 33:59.458
THE, UH -- THE FACT
HUNTER'S LEAVING.

33:59.542 --> 34:01.959
THERE'S NOTHING
TO TALK ABOUT.

34:03.875 --> 34:07.166
IT'S GONNA
FEEL LIKE CRAP...

34:07.250 --> 34:10.458
WALKING PAST HIS ROOM
AND HIM NOT BEING THERE.

34:10.542 --> 34:13.709
THE WHOLE PLACE IS GONNA FEEL
EMPTY WITHOUT HIM.

34:13.792 --> 34:15.166
IT'S SO STUPID.

34:15.250 --> 34:17.041
I'VE KNOWN THE GUY,
WHAT, A FEW DAYS?

34:17.125 --> 34:18.917
NO, NO, IT'S NOT STUPID.
IT'S NOT.

34:19.000 --> 34:22.625
I THINK IT'S A SIGN.

34:22.709 --> 34:24.792
YOU'VE CHANGED.

34:24.875 --> 34:27.959
WHETHER YOU LIKE IT
OR NOT.

34:28.041 --> 34:30.625
FALLING IN...

34:30.709 --> 34:33.458
LOVE CAN DO THAT
TO A PERSON.

34:33.542 --> 34:35.792
YOU DON'T SEE IT,
BUT <i>WE</i> DO, YOU KNOW?

34:35.875 --> 34:36.875
<i>I</i> DO.

34:39.500 --> 34:43.667
I STILL DON'T
WANT TO GO INSIDE.

34:45.250 --> 34:48.125
WHAT DO YOU WANT TO DO?

35:12.083 --> 35:13.834
KIDDING ME?!

35:13.917 --> 35:15.458
[ SIGHS ]

35:19.458 --> 35:23.041
[ LOCK TURNS ]

35:23.125 --> 35:24.375
OKAY.

35:24.458 --> 35:26.000
[ PANTING ]

35:26.083 --> 35:27.750
[ Ringing ]

35:27.834 --> 35:29.375
PLEASE PICK UP, LEO.
PLEASE PICK UP.

35:29.458 --> 35:31.834
<i>Hey, this is Leo.</i>
<i>Leave a message --</i>

35:35.375 --> 35:36.792
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

35:36.875 --> 35:38.959
OKAY, OKAY.

35:52.166 --> 35:54.041
[ COUGHS ]

35:57.709 --> 35:59.041
[ GRUNTS ]

35:59.125 --> 36:01.625
HEY, WHAT'S GOING ON?
IS YOUR LEG ACTING UP?

36:01.709 --> 36:04.041
UM, NO,
IT'S NOT <i>TOO</i> BAD.

36:04.125 --> 36:07.375
IT MAY BE FROM LYING
ON THAT MACHINE FOR SO LONG.

36:07.458 --> 36:09.583
ALL RIGHT, WELL, IF YOU WANT, WE
CAN GET YOU SOME PAIN-KILLERS.

36:09.667 --> 36:11.959
NO, NO,
I'M -- I'M OKAY.

36:12.041 --> 36:14.917
OKAY.
WHAT'S UP?

36:15.000 --> 36:17.417
I JUST GOT OFF THE PHONE
WITH YOUR SOCIAL WORKER, MEGAN.

36:17.500 --> 36:18.709
WHAT ABOUT?

36:18.792 --> 36:20.208
LIKE I SAID,
YOUR SURGERY IS RISKY.

36:20.291 --> 36:21.959
THE STATE DOESN'T
WANT TO TAKE ANY RISKS,

36:22.041 --> 36:22.959
ESPECIALLY WITH A MINOR.

36:23.041 --> 36:24.458
EMANCIPATED MINOR.

36:24.542 --> 36:26.000
THAT'S JUST IT.
YOU'RE NOT EMANCIPATED YET.

36:26.083 --> 36:28.375
I-I DON'T UNDERSTAND.
OKAY, H-HERE'S THE DEAL.

36:28.458 --> 36:30.083
CALIFORNIA
CHILDREN'S SERVICES

36:30.166 --> 36:33.583
WILL NOT ALLOW ME TO PERFORM
THE SURGERY AT THIS TIME.

36:33.667 --> 36:37.000
THEY WANT YOU TO GO THROUGH
ANOTHER CYCLE OF CHEMOTHERAPY.

36:39.041 --> 36:40.417
NO, WHAT IF I --
WHAT IF I REFUSE?

36:40.500 --> 36:41.959
WHAT IF I SAY
I WON'T DO THE CHEMO?

36:42.041 --> 36:43.875
YOUR TUMORS
ARE GONNA GROW BACK.

36:43.959 --> 36:45.291
YOU DON'T HAVE A CHOICE,
JORDI,

36:45.375 --> 36:47.917
UNTIL YOU'RE OFFICIALLY
EMANCIPATED.

36:48.000 --> 36:51.583
AND WHAT IF I CAN MAKE THAT
HAPPEN, LIKE, IMMEDIATELY?

36:51.667 --> 36:54.208
WHAT? HOW -- HOW FAR ALONG
ARE YOU IN THE PROCESS?

36:54.291 --> 36:56.000
I HAVE EVERYTHING.

36:56.083 --> 36:58.125
IT'S JUST THE APPLICATION
THAT NEEDS TO BE PROCESSED.

36:58.208 --> 36:59.917
I CAN EXPEDITE THAT.
OKAY.

37:00.000 --> 37:01.458
GIVE ME ONE OR TWO DAYS TO SEE
IF I CAN MAKE THIS WORK.

37:01.542 --> 37:03.458
ALL RIGHT, JORDI,
YOU HAVE 24 HOURS.

37:03.542 --> 37:04.959
I'M SORRY.
THAT'S ALL I'M COMFORTABLE WITH.

37:05.041 --> 37:07.333
Y-YOUR TUMORS
ARE TOO AGGRESSIVE.

37:07.417 --> 37:09.166
IT'S OKAY.

37:09.250 --> 37:12.417
NO PROBLEM.
I'LL MAKE IT HAPPEN.

37:12.500 --> 37:14.959
ALL RIGHT, GOOD.
HEY, DOC.

37:16.291 --> 37:18.625
MY LEG HURTS MORE
THAN I THOUGHT.

37:18.709 --> 37:20.000
WOULD IT BE OKAY --

37:20.083 --> 37:21.750
YEAH.
YEAH, YEAH, YEAH.

37:21.834 --> 37:24.000
I'LL, UH, I'LL HAVE KENJI BRING
YOU IN SOMETHING, AND, UM...

37:24.083 --> 37:26.125
GET A GOOD NIGHT'S SLEEP.

37:26.208 --> 37:29.166
I WILL.

37:38.667 --> 37:40.417
[ Ringing ]

37:40.500 --> 37:41.917
ALEXA: Hello?

37:42.000 --> 37:44.417
HEY. ALEXA?
Jordi?

37:44.500 --> 37:47.250
MEET ME OUTSIDE THE HOSPITAL
IN AN HOUR.

37:48.542 --> 37:51.125
OH, UH...

37:51.208 --> 37:53.417
I'M SORRY.
I-I THOUGHT YOU WERE...

37:53.500 --> 37:55.125
Charlie:
<i>LEAVING? HE</i> WAS.

37:55.208 --> 37:57.250
<i>BUT I HAVE MY REASONS</i>
<i>FOR WANTING HIM TO STAY.</i>

37:57.333 --> 37:58.917
TURNS OUT THE KID
IS MUCH BETTER

37:59.000 --> 38:00.417
AT, UH, CHECKERS
THAN HE IS AT CHESS.

38:00.500 --> 38:02.750
ONE GAME TURNED
INTO TWO OUT OF THREE,

38:02.834 --> 38:05.583
AND THEN THREE
OUT OF FIVE AND...

38:10.166 --> 38:11.917
[ CHUCKLES ]

38:12.000 --> 38:13.250
"I WON."

38:13.333 --> 38:15.625
SPELLED "O-N-E."

38:15.709 --> 38:18.291
GOOD KID, BAD SPELLER.

38:18.375 --> 38:20.959
<i>HEY, DO I HARP ON</i> YOUR <i>FLAWS?</i>

38:21.041 --> 38:22.417
BUSY DAY, CHARLIE.

38:22.500 --> 38:23.333
IS IT OKAY TO SHUT THIS DOWN
FOR THE NIGHT?

38:23.417 --> 38:25.125
[ <i>CLICKING</i> ]

38:25.208 --> 38:28.917
ALL RIGHT.

38:29.000 --> 38:30.542
IT'S AMAZING.

38:30.625 --> 38:35.333
FOR SO LONG, I'VE PRAYED FOR HIM
TO OPEN HIS EYES,

38:35.417 --> 38:37.667
AND NOW THAT HE DOES...

38:37.750 --> 38:38.750
IT'S NOT ENOUGH.

38:38.834 --> 38:41.417
I KNOW.
IT'S GREEDY.

38:41.500 --> 38:43.583
NO. IT'S HUMAN NATURE.

38:43.667 --> 38:47.667
AS SOON AS WE GET WHAT WE WANT,
WE WANT MORE.

38:47.750 --> 38:49.667
WE PUSH THE BOUNDARIES.
WE TEST THE LIMITS.

38:49.750 --> 38:51.834
SOMEONE ASKS
TO COOK YOU DINNER,

38:51.917 --> 38:53.750
AND YOU RUIN IT
BY ASKING FOR DRINKS.
WAIT, THAT'S NOT WHAT --

38:53.834 --> 38:56.667
OKAY, I <i>WANTED</i> TO ASK YOU
TO DINNER --

38:56.750 --> 38:58.250
AND CHARLIE
<i>WANTS</i> TO GET BETTER.

38:58.333 --> 39:00.000
THERE'S JUST SOMETHING
BLOCKING HIM.

39:00.083 --> 39:01.709
IT'S MY JOB
TO FIND OUT WHAT.

39:01.792 --> 39:04.250
UNFORTUNATELY,
THE SAME DOES NOT APPLY TO YOU.

39:04.333 --> 39:06.291
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

39:06.375 --> 39:08.166
IT MEANS I'M NOT
GONNA PUSH YOU, DENA.

39:08.250 --> 39:10.166
IF YOU DON'T FIND ME
ATTRACTIVE, THEN --

39:10.250 --> 39:12.250
NO, NO, NO, NO.
THAT'S NOT THE PROBLEM.

39:12.333 --> 39:13.750
THEN WHAT
<i>IS</i> THE PROBLEM?

39:13.834 --> 39:15.417
WE WORK TOGETHER.

39:15.500 --> 39:17.208
I'VE...

39:17.291 --> 39:20.250
LEARNED FROM EXPERIENCE
WHEN TWO PEOPLE WORK TOGETHER,

39:20.333 --> 39:23.333
IT'S BETTER TO KEEP THINGS
STRICTLY PROFESSIONAL.

39:23.417 --> 39:27.166
YOU KNOW,
TO [SIGHS] AVOID...

39:27.250 --> 39:29.500
WEIRDNESS.

39:29.583 --> 39:30.709
WEIRDNESS?

39:30.792 --> 39:32.625
IT'S A MEDICAL TERM.

39:32.709 --> 39:34.208
AH.

39:34.291 --> 39:38.250
PROFESSIONALISM IS, YEAH,
I-IT'S IMPORTANT.

39:38.333 --> 39:41.041
I COULDN'T AGREE MORE.
GOOD.

39:42.125 --> 39:44.125
[ GASPS ]

39:44.208 --> 39:46.709
<i>AND THEN THE</i> OTHER <i>GREAT</i>
<i>PHILOSOPHER, BIGGIE SMALLS,</i>

39:46.792 --> 39:48.792
<i>TAUGHT ME THIS --</i>

39:48.875 --> 39:53.709
<i>NEVER LET THEM KNOW</i>
<i>YOUR NEXT MOVE.</i>

39:53.792 --> 39:56.375
SO, WHAT I WANT IS
A RAPID SEQUENCE INDUCTION.

39:56.458 --> 39:58.041
♪ WOKE UP LOST
IN A WORLD I DIDN'T KNOW ♪

39:58.125 --> 40:00.542
HEY, HUNTER,
LET'S TRY COUNTING BACKWARDS.

40:00.625 --> 40:01.875
WAIT, WHOSE IS IT?

40:01.959 --> 40:03.208
♪ I SHOOK IT OFF AND ♪
PARDON?

40:03.291 --> 40:04.792
THE LIVER.
WHO DID IT COME FROM?

40:04.875 --> 40:06.875
♪ I'M TRYING TO MAKE A GO ♪

40:06.959 --> 40:10.000
♪ EVER GET THE FEELING ♪
I JUST NEED A NAME.

40:10.083 --> 40:12.000
♪ THAT THE STORY ISN'T DONE ♪

40:12.083 --> 40:16.417
♪ AND YOU KNOW THAT YOU ARE NOT
THE ONLY ONE ♪

40:16.500 --> 40:18.834
STEVEN KAMINSKY.

40:18.917 --> 40:20.542
[ SIGHS ]
STEVEN KAMINSKY.

40:20.625 --> 40:22.041
♪ AND I KNOW
YOU'RE OUT THERE SOMEWHERE ♪

40:22.125 --> 40:23.750
OKAY. THANK YOU.

40:23.834 --> 40:25.250
♪ AND I KNOW THAT YOU ARE WELL ♪
COUNTING BACK.

40:25.333 --> 40:26.375
♪ LOOKING FOR AN ANSWER ♪

40:26.458 --> 40:28.542
10...9...

40:28.625 --> 40:31.709
♪ THAT ONLY TIME CAN TELL ♪

40:31.792 --> 40:33.709
♪ BUT SOMETHING DOWN INSIDE ME ♪

40:33.792 --> 40:36.709
♪ MAKES ME THINK
THERE'S SOMETHING MORE ♪

40:36.792 --> 40:39.375
♪ AND I DON'T HAVE ANY PROOF ♪

40:39.458 --> 40:43.333
♪ BUT I'M SURE ♪

40:43.417 --> 40:46.000
♪ AND I KNOW
YOU'RE OUT THERE SOMEWHERE ♪

40:46.083 --> 40:49.667
♪ AND I KNOW THAT YOU ARE WELL ♪

40:49.750 --> 40:52.500
♪ LOOKING FOR AN ANSWER ♪

40:52.583 --> 40:55.458
♪ BUT ONLY TIME CAN TELL ♪
[ ZIPPER OPENS ]

40:55.542 --> 40:57.709
KARA...MY LEG.

40:57.792 --> 40:59.500
WHAT ABOUT IT?

40:59.583 --> 41:03.041
I'VE NEVER DONE THIS...
LIKE THIS.

41:03.125 --> 41:04.458
SO?

41:04.542 --> 41:06.083
IT MIGHT LOOK...

41:06.166 --> 41:09.041
I DON'T CARE.
DO YOU?

41:09.125 --> 41:12.375
♪ MM-MM-HMM ♪

41:12.458 --> 41:16.166
[ MONITOR BEEPING ]

41:16.250 --> 41:20.917
WE MAY HAVE TO RECONSTRUCT
THE VENA CAVA.

41:23.542 --> 41:26.458
♪ WOKE UP LOST ♪

41:26.542 --> 41:28.709
♪ IN A WORLD I CAN'T ESCAPE ♪
LOOKS GOOD.

41:28.792 --> 41:32.709
♪ WHAT I'LL BECOME ♪

41:32.792 --> 41:35.375
♪ IS SLOWLY TAKING SHAPE ♪

41:35.458 --> 41:36.709
♪ START AGAIN IS NOT THE END ♪

41:36.792 --> 41:38.875
RETRACT.

41:38.959 --> 41:41.542
♪ BUT ALTOGETHER NEW ♪

41:41.625 --> 41:44.083
♪ AND I'M NEVER GIVING UP ♪

41:44.166 --> 41:47.583
♪ TILL I FIND YOU ♪

41:47.667 --> 41:50.417
♪ AND I KNOW
YOU'RE OUT THERE SOMEWHERE ♪

41:50.500 --> 41:54.083
♪ AND I KNOW THAT YOU ARE WELL ♪

41:54.166 --> 41:56.917
♪ LOOKING FOR AN ANSWER ♪

41:57.000 --> 41:58.125
♪ BUT ONLY TIME CAN TELL ♪

41:58.208 --> 41:59.583
GOOD NIGHT, JORDI.
GOOD NIGHT.

41:59.667 --> 42:02.000
THANKS.
♪ PARALLELS ♪

42:05.208 --> 42:08.041
♪ PARALLELS ♪

42:17.083 --> 42:19.792
[ SCRAPING ]

42:24.333 --> 42:27.041
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]
Jon: EMMA, MAY I COME IN?

42:29.125 --> 42:32.041
EMMA.

42:32.125 --> 42:34.291
ARE YOU IN HERE, SWEETIE?

42:36.875 --> 42:38.458
EMMA?

42:38.542 --> 42:41.792
EMMA!
EMMA, OPEN THIS DOOR!

42:41.875 --> 42:42.959
EMMA!

42:43.041 --> 42:45.792
[ GRUNTS ]

42:45.875 --> 42:48.000
CAROLINE!
